          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer423674631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10852652282645011796">Somehow or another, I&apos;d failed to add this when I was compiling my life-time bookshelf, but I&apos;m happy to rectify the error. Whether you&apos;re atheist, agnostic, or theist, Comte-Sponville&apos;s elegant apologia (in the classical sense--explanation more than apology) will force you to rethink the ethical implications of where you stand. I&apos;ll leave it there and let C-S speak for himself, but this is as good a book on the spiritual/ethical life as I&apos;ve ever read.</span>
  <span id="freeText10852652282645011796" style="display:none">Somehow or another, I'd failed to add this when I was compiling my life-time bookshelf, but I'm happy to rectify the error. Whether you're atheist, agnostic, or theist, Comte-Sponville's elegant apologia (in the classical sense--explanation more than apology) will force you to rethink the ethical implications of where you stand. I'll leave it there and let C-S speak for himself, but this is as good a book on the spiritual/ethical life as I've ever read.</span>
