        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2794466612" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3888919018220901513">I have never read much philosophy. This small book referenced dozens of philosophers I&apos;ve heard of but knew little about. The author was interesting on the subjects of why he does not believe in God, the arguments made by those of faith for God&apos;s existence, and why he has arrived at the belief that religion has little value. In chapter 3, the author got into a very involved explanation of his conception of atheist spirituality--why it is possible even without believing in a god, and what form th</span>
  <span id="freeText3888919018220901513" style="display:none">I have never read much philosophy. This small book referenced dozens of philosophers I've heard of but knew little about. The author was interesting on the subjects of why he does not believe in God, the arguments made by those of faith for God's existence, and why he has arrived at the belief that religion has little value. In chapter 3, the author got into a very involved explanation of his conception of atheist spirituality--why it is possible even without believing in a god, and what form that spirituality takes.<br />I hope he enjoyed writing it. I found myself getting tangled up in his discussion of infinity, relativity, absolutes, temporality, oneness and so on. I got the gist of his idea, but it was tough going.<br />Back to fiction and history for me...</span>
  <a data-text-id="3888919018220901513" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
