        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3830010569" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1137227491071434003">So my reality for this book is 3.5 stars, but I am rounding down because the book was a little unclear, confusing, and wordy at times. <br/>It was an interesting read overall though and it reminded me how much I do actually like philosophy reasons. It was only a few chapters but was broken into manageable subheadings in each chapter. There were points that made me stop and think, and topics I want to read into more. It was not a bad book in general, but it did not give me full clarity for my own beli</span>
  <span id="freeText1137227491071434003" style="display:none">So my reality for this book is 3.5 stars, but I am rounding down because the book was a little unclear, confusing, and wordy at times. <br />It was an interesting read overall though and it reminded me how much I do actually like philosophy reasons. It was only a few chapters but was broken into manageable subheadings in each chapter. There were points that made me stop and think, and topics I want to read into more. It was not a bad book in general, but it did not give me full clarity for my own beliefs, rather, it raised more questions. I definitely want to read more about religions and spirituality at this point though.</span>
