        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3726723314?book_show_action=true">Dec 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hafidha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hafidha" href="/user/show/1953135-hafidha">Hafidha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3726723314" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16547035700075534022">Pretty boring book but I give three stars because it might be of use to some young atheist grappling with nihilism... and because the white covered edition I have is quite adorable -- and also the layout is fantastic and makes this dry text as readable as one could hope for. I appreciate what the book attempts to do (make the case for a kinder gentler atheism during an obnoxious public phase of prominent white male jerk atheism), but there is nothing interesting in here, Comte-Sponville&apos;s world </span>
  <span id="freeText16547035700075534022" style="display:none">Pretty boring book but I give three stars because it might be of use to some young atheist grappling with nihilism... and because the white covered edition I have is quite adorable -- and also the layout is fantastic and makes this dry text as readable as one could hope for. I appreciate what the book attempts to do (make the case for a kinder gentler atheism during an obnoxious public phase of prominent white male jerk atheism), but there is nothing interesting in here, Comte-Sponville's world is so small and limited. Has he spent most of his life in a study? This book doesn't compare at all to the philosophy and spiritual essays I've read by atheist writers, preachers and freethinkers.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16547035700075534022" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


