<span id="freeTextContainer5868107803988277878">I largely enjoyed this book, up to the point where the author recounts his own spiritual experiences. Something like that is automatically hard to put into words, but I felt that he sounded too much like a New Age guru at that point.<br/><br/>By and large a good explanation of why you can be an atheist and still see more than the material world.</span>

          </span>
